parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the transmission can cause the vehicle to stall, lose power, or become stuck in gear, leading to accidents or leaving the driver stranded.
symptoms: The vehicle stalls or loses power
the transmission hesitates or fails to engage
the vehicle is unable to shift into gear
the transmission warning light is illuminated
the vehicle makes abnormal noises or vibrations.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the powertrain can cause the vehicle to lose power, stall, or become stuck in gear, leading to accidents or leaving the driver stranded.
symptoms: The vehicle loses power
the engine warning light is illuminated
the vehicle stalls or hesitates
the transmission warning light is illuminated
the vehicle makes abnormal noises or vibrations.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The delay in repairing recalled vehicles can lead to continued safety risks for drivers and passengers.
symptoms: The vehicle is subject to a recall
but the repair parts are not available
the manufacturer has exceeded a reasonable time for the recall repair
the vehicle has not been repaired despite multiple attempts.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the fuel door release button can cause inconvenience and safety risks, as the driver may be unable to refuel the vehicle.
symptoms: The fuel door release button does not work
prohibiting the driver from opening the fuel door.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the vehicle horn can cause safety concerns, as the driver may be unable to alert pedestrians, other vehicles, or animals to their presence.
symptoms: The vehicle horn stops working or works intermittently.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The vehicle rolling away from the driver can cause accidents, injuries, or fatalities.
symptoms: The vehicle rolls away from the driver
often while they are outside the vehicle
and can cause damage or injury.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the auto start/stop system can cause inconvenience and safety risks, as the vehicle may stall or lose power while driving.
symptoms: The vehicle stumbles or completely stops the engine while driving
often when the auto start/stop system is engaged.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The shattering of the panoramic sunroof can cause safety risks, as the driver and passengers may be injured by broken glass.
symptoms: The panoramic sunroof shatters or cracks without any apparent cause
often while driving.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Transmission and powertrain issues can cause safety risks, as the vehicle may lose power or stall while driving.
symptoms: The vehicle loses power
stalls
or has difficulty shifting gears.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The inverter coolant warning can cause inconvenience and safety risks, as the driver may be unaware of the actual coolant level.
symptoms: The vehicle displays a "refill inverter coolant" warning
often despite the coolant level being normal.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the jacking and lift system can cause safety risks, as the vehicle may fall off the jack or lift.
symptoms: The vehicle rocks or falls off the jack or lift
often while the driver is underneath.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Unknown shaking or vibrations can cause safety risks, as the driver may lose control of the vehicle.
symptoms: The vehicle experiences unknown shaking or vibrations
often while driving.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Recall issues can cause safety risks, as the vehicle may not be properly repaired or maintained.
symptoms: The vehicle has an outstanding recall
but the manufacturer has not provided a remedy or solution.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The sharp edge on the passenger door can cause injury, as passengers may cut themselves on the door.
symptoms: The passenger door has a sharp edge
which can cause cuts or injuries.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Engine stalling can cause safety risks, as the vehicle may lose power while driving.
symptoms: The engine stalls or loses power
often while driving.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The intermittent stalling of the engine can cause the vehicle to lose power, increasing the risk of a crash, especially when driving on a highway.
symptoms: The engine stalls while driving
the vehicle loses power
the warning lights on the dashboard illuminate
the vehicle shudders before stalling
the engine stalls when the Idle Stop and Go (ISG) feature is on.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the electrical system can cause the dashboard to go black, disabling the driver's ability to view important instruments, and can also cause the safety features to malfunction, increasing the risk of a crash.
symptoms: The dashboard goes black
the safety features such as lane assist and lane departure warning malfunction
the horn stops working
the brakes slam on for no reason.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The malfunction of the seat can cause the driver to be pinned against the steering wheel, restricting breathing and potentially causing injuries.
symptoms: The driver's seat moves forward and reclines into the dash without input from the operator
pinning the driver against the steering wheel.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the battery can cause the vehicle to stall, increasing the risk of a crash, and can also cause the electrical systems to malfunction, leading to a loss of power and safety features.
symptoms: The battery is dead
the vehicle will not start
the battery is too low to activate lights or locks
the vehicle's electrical systems malfunction.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the clutch and gearbox can cause the vehicle to lose power, making it difficult to shift gears, which can lead to accidents or leave the driver stranded.
symptoms: The clutch pedal feels soft or spongy
the clutch pedal sticks to the floor
the clutch pedal does not return to its normal position
the vehicle is unable to shift into gear.
